  "text": "To initialize the filters for training, we used the following standard procedure [CITATION_1] . We first spotted the location of potential spikes using a pre-computed threshold and windowed the data around the spotted positions. Then, we computed the two first principal components of the matrix whose rows comprise the obtained windows. Finally, we performed k-means clustering on the windows in principal-component space and picked the initial filters as the center of the clusters. Figure 9 shows the results of training CRsAE on the extracellular data. The initial filters are in gray color (denoted by ) and learned filters are in red color (denoted by ). The figure shows that CRsAE is able to learn filters that resemble true action potentials.",
